 minuscule but immensely wealthy and influential corporate elite. Thanks to this dysfunctional environment, Suarez-Villa argues, stagnation and a vanishing public trust have become the hallmarks of our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCorporate governance. 0aOligopolies. 0aState, The. 4aBusiness and Economics : Economic History. 4aBusiness and Economics : Economy and Society. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Economy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Sociology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Economic Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2014z978311149015140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845487040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438454870423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438454870/original  a978-3-11-149015-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles